Date of publication: 31 August 2023
URL: https://www2.swift.com/mystandards/#/mp/mx/_ozvbgCxpEeyCOPAtSa9DrA/_WqND8VwkEeyQB5auwXHO8w
Description: Fedwire Funds Service Scope

A message reject is the message the Fedwire Funds Service and Fedwire Funds participants use to respectively inform a Fedwire Funds participant or the Fedwire Funds Service that a message they previously sent has been rejected. 

Fedwire Funds Service Usage

For value messages (i.e., pacs.008, pacs.009, pacs.004) and certain nonvalue messages (i.e., pain.013, camt.056) the message reject will only be used to communicate technical rejection reasons, e.g., a message not passing the syntax validation.   

To communicate business validation rejection reasons the payment status report (pacs.002) will be used for value messages, and for nonvalue messages the request for payment response (pain.014) and the return request response (camt.029) will be used for the drawdown request (pain.013) and return request (camt.056) respectively. 

For all other messages in scope of the Fedwire Funds Service migration to ISO 20022 the message reject will be used to inform of both technical and business validation rejection reasons. 
